text: Wangenbourg-Engenthal is a commune. It is in Grand Est in the Bas-Rhin department in northeast France. It was created on 1 November 1974 from the former communes of Engenthal and Wangenbourg. == Hamlets == The commune has eight hamlets: * Engenthal-le-Bas * Engenthal-le-Haut * Freudeneck * les Huttes * Obersteigen * Schneethal * Windsbourg * Wolfsthal == References == Category:Communes in Bas-Rhin
title: Wangenbourg-Engenthal
